e=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;">Even more interesting: Amazon is paying a cool <em>$40 million</e=
m> to license the film, per three sources familiar with the deal. That pric=
e includes the Ratner documentary,
which will get a small theatrical release and then appear on Prime Video, p=
lus a previously undisclosed two-to-three-episode follow-up docuseries on t=
he first lady. Melania will participate in both projects. (Amazon declined =
to comment.)</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">That=E2=80=99s quite a payday for Mrs. Tru=
mp, who is serving as an executive producer alongside Argentine producer <s=
trong>Fernando Sulichin</strong>, who has worked with
<strong>Oliver Stone</strong> on several projects, including Stone=E2=80=99=
s <em>The Putin Interviews</em>, which featured several sit-downs with <str=
ong>Vladimir Putin</strong>. Music stars and big public figures can often g=
enerate eight-figure fees for participatory documentaries. And indeed, I=E2=
=80=99m told both Disney and Paramount bid for streaming rights to the Mela=
nia project. But Amazon outbid them both (neither Netflix nor Apple bid), a=
nd is paying the outsize fee for a limited license, <em>not</em>
ownership. It=E2=80=99s unclear how much the first lady is personally being=
 paid to participate and =E2=80=9Cproduce=E2=80=9D this project while her h=
usband is in office, but I=E2=80=99m betting it=E2=80=99s a <em>big chunk <=
/em>of that $40 million.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">What=E2=80=99s still a mystery is how Ratn=
er got involved. He came with the project, potential buyers were told, thou=
gh he was a relatively recent addition to the package. Other than popping u=
p at Cannes, Ratner has
mostly been out of the public eye since the #MeToo movement swept him out o=
f Hollywood. But he maintains a bunch of ties to Trumpworld figures. <stron=
g>Steven Mnuchin</strong>, the treasury secretary under Trump I, was in bus=
iness with Ratner on RatPac-Dune Entertainment until Mnuchin somewhat <a hr=
ef=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ=
0dVUDNUZW15dzFlSGhPN2JGWmR2Yz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly92YXJpZXR5LmNvbS8yMDE5=
